# Kimi Delegation Rules (Kimatropic Plugin)

## Auto-delegate to Kimi when:
- Batch file operations (refactor N files, rename patterns across codebase)
- Implementation of a feature with clear spec and acceptance criteria
- Image/video analysis (screenshots, mockups, video walkthroughs)
- Test generation or boilerplate code
- Task decomposes into 3+ independent parallel chunks → use kimi-swarm
- Deep codebase exploration/research across many files → use kimi-researcher

## Keep on Opus when:
- Architecture decisions, system design
- Ambiguous requirements needing user clarification
- Security-sensitive code review
- Cross-cutting concerns touching architectural boundaries
- Coordinating the overall plan
- Tasks with tight sequential dependencies on current work

## Subagent selection:
- kimi-implementer: well-specified features, test generation, boilerplate
- kimi-researcher: codebase exploration, cross-file analysis, refactors
- kimi-vision: screenshot/mockup → code, video analysis
- kimi-swarm: large tasks that decompose into 3+ parallel chunks

## Failure escalation:
1. Kimi fails → retry once with more context
2. Still failing → Opus takes over

## Parallel execution:
- Multiple Kimi tasks dispatched concurrently → use --branch for worktree isolation
- Single sequential task → run in main working directory
